{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":13338,"record_hash":"sha256:ff6b88c80ac13aa154daf66347dc1b554f3dfe75f7577349ebdc8dea8ae2860d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T22:22:12.504Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Validate target before transcript work\\\" body=\\\"`--target` is cheap CLI input, but it stays a `String` until `write_capture`, after repo discovery, transcript canonicalization/read, JSON parsing, and cwd validation. Parse it earlier and pass a `Target` down so invalid targets fail first and the writer does less boundary work.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=39 priority=2 confidence=0.88}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Reuse cwd validation output\\\" body=\\\"`capture` validates all transcript cwd values, discards the canonicalized result, then re-iterates the transcript to pick the first raw cwd for GitMeta. Have `validate_cwds` return the accepted cwd value to store, preserving current raw-vs-canonical semantics deliberately.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs\\\" start=35 end=37 priority=3 confidence=0.82}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Collapse duplicate dedupe state if possible\\\" body=\\\"The writer maintains both `seen-record-hashes` and a transcript list that embeds the same `source_record_hash`, then reads both to decide what is new. If no consumer truly needs `records_new` separately from appended transcript records, using the transcript list as the single source of truth would delete a set key, one GitMeta read, one per-run set, and the backfill distinction.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=42 end=67 priority=3 confidence=0.72}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Remove misleading duplicated session scalar\\\" body=\\\"The GitMeta key named `session-id` stores `session_key`, while that same key is already part of the GitMeta key prefix. Unless another reader depends on it, deleting this scalar is clearer than storing one fact twice under two names.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=190 end=192 priority=3 confidence=0.84}\\n\\n**Trace**\\n`but agentlog capture` is registered in [args/mod.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/args/mod.rs:1119), then special-cased before app settings and metrics in [but/src/lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:150). That calls `but_agentlog::run_from_current_dir` at [but/src/lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:1477).\\n\\nInside `but-agentlog`, [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:47) parses `agent`, validates empty transcript path, discovers/canonicalizes the repo workdir, resolves relative transcript paths, and calls `capture`. [capture.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:29) canonicalizes/reads the transcript, hashes/parses it, validates cwd values, builds `GitMetaCaptureInput`, and calls `write_capture`. [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:39) parses the target, opens GitMeta, reads dedupe state, appends transcript envelopes, and writes scalar metadata.\\n\\nThe only repo “rediscovery” I’d be cautious about changing is `gix::discover` in CLI followed by `Session::open(repo_path)` in GitMeta. Since `git-meta-lib` owns the session/store opening, I would leave that unless it exposes a clean `Session::from_repo`-style API. No files edited and no tests run, per the read-only review request.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T22:22:12.504Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"<su