ril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=190 end=192 priority=3 confidence=0.84}\\n\\n**Trace**\\n`but agentlog capture` is registered in [args/mod.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/args/mod.rs:1119), then special-cased before app settings and metrics in [but/src/lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:150). That calls `but_agentlog::run_from_current_dir` at [but/src/lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:1477).\\n\\nInside `but-agentlog`, [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:47) parses `agent`, validates empty transcript path, discovers/canonicalizes the repo workdir, resolves relative transcript paths, and calls `capture`. [capture.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:29) canonicalizes/reads the transcript, hashes/parses it, validates cwd values, builds `GitMetaCaptureInput`, and calls `write_capture`. [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:39) parses the target, opens GitMeta, reads dedupe state, appends transcript envelopes, and writes scalar metadata.\\n\\nThe only repo “rediscovery” I’d be cautious about changing is `gix::discover` in CLI followed by `Session::open(repo_path)` in GitMeta. Since `git-meta-lib` owns the session/store opening, I would leave that unless it exposes a clean `Session::from_repo`-style API. No files edited and no tests run, per the read-only review request.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>"}]}}}